CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, January 24, 1938, pg. unknown, reads: "Helen Phillips another Pgh. debbie seems to have the other end of the Lewis family well in tow, for here she is smiling and happy with the brother of John Henry, Joel Lewis by name, and a Howard Univ. med stude by choice. The CARAVAN just dotes on these romances and the charming Helen makes quite a few of the local lad's hearts turn over when she smiles ever so sweetly.  (Photo by 'Teenie' Harris)."
TitMainTitle: Helen Phillips and Joel Lewis posed in front of window
